**Root cause:**
- The context free list (`freelistProfilerContext`) is not cleared/reset during `profiler_disable`/`flush_unmatched`.
- If any context is added to the free list before disable (for instance, by `ptrace_leave_call`), its memory will be freed in `flush_unmatched`, but the pointer lingers in the free list and will be reused later, causing use-after-free.

