After freeing all active contexts in `flush_unmatched`, we must also _clear the free list_ (`freelistProfilerContext = NULL;`), and ensure that any items in the free list during/after disable are freed too, not just active contexts.

But, `clearEntries` already does this, suggesting the logic needs to be replicated or reused in `flush_unmatched`. But the only call to `clearEntries` resets the tree, not in `profiler_disable`.

So, in `flush_unmatched`, we should free out both the context chain and the free list (`freelistProfilerContext`).

